subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Male (
holotype
).

Habitus as in 
Fig. 1A
. Total length 5.5. Prosoma 1.5 long, 1.6 wide. Diameter of AME 120 µm, ALE 170 µm, PME 160 µm, PLE 150 µm. AME–AME 70 µm, PME–PME 240 µm, PME–ALE 40 µm. Chelicera (
Fig. 2A–B
) with thumb-like proximo-lateral apophysis (left one broken), small, ventrally curved frontal apophysis, and ventrally curved, notched triangular distal apophysis longer than proximo-lateral apophysis. Opisthosoma 3.8 long, 2.0 wide. Leg Ⅰ 50.4 (12.8 + 0.7 + 13.0 + 21.4 + 2.5), leg II 33.5 (9.2 + 0.7 + 8.6 + 13.5 + 1.5), leg III 22.6 (6.6 + 0.6 + 5.5 + 8.7 + 1.2), leg IV 30.0 (8.7 + 0.8 + 7.5 + 11.6 + 1.4). Ratio of leg Ⅰ (18.0: 1.0: 18.3: 30.1: 3.5), leg II (13.1: 1.0: 12.3: 19.2: 2.2), leg III (11.9: 1.0: 10.1: 15.7: 2.1), leg IV (11.4: 1.0: 8.8: 15.2: 1.8). Leg formula 1243. Tibia Ⅰ L/d 81. Retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia Ⅰ at 6% proximally. Tarsus I with 22 pseudosegments. For the other somatic features see description of the species-group above. Palp (
Fig. 3
). Trochanter apophysis as long as femur, slender, distinctly elongated and strongly curved, distally blunt and folded once, proximo-retrolaterally with tubercle (
Fig. 3A–B
); femur ventrally swollen; tibia with prolatero-ventral tubercle; procursus (
Fig. 3B
) dark brown, slightly sinuated dorsally, with moderate ventral knee; dorso-subdistal portion of procursus slightly swollen, with one short hair and two spines (
Fig. 3B, D
); procursus tip (
Fig. 3C–E
) with four ridges retrolaterally, finger-like, distally blunt dorsal process directed prolaterally (arrowed 
1 in
Fig. 3D
), membranous prolateral process with two blunt projections distally (arrowed 
2 in
Fig. 3D
), and pointed triangular ventral process (arrowed in 
Fig. 3E
); genital bulb round, pale yellow; uncus (
Fig. 3F
) dark brown, lingulate, outer proximal margin extended roundly without scales, outer distal margin curved and inner margin almost linear, with many tiny scales; pseudoappendix (
Fig. 3G
) tiny, slender and blunt, hidden by uncus prolaterally; embolus (
Fig. 3G
) pale yellow, slender and distally fringed, weakly sclerotized, about 1.5 times as long as uncus.

An intrapopulational variation was observed on the length of dorso-subdistal spines and dorsal process, and shapes of projections of membranous prolateral process in procursus tip (
Fig. 13A, D, G, J
).

Females. Prosoma width: 1.4–1.7 (mean 1.6), tibia Ⅰ: 8.1–9.0 (mean 8.5) (n=6). An intrapopulational variation was observed on the size of pore plates of internal genitalia (
Fig. 13C, F, I, L
), but the epigynal shapes were largely consistent (
Fig. 13B, E, H, K
).
